1
00:00:08,590 --> 00:00:09,580
This isn’t real.

2
00:00:09,950 --> 00:00:10,850
Why?

3
00:00:12,270 --> 00:00:15,010
Goodbye, my P’ Le.

4
00:00:16,480 --> 00:00:17,620
Finally cremated.

5
00:00:17,640 --> 00:00:21,080
I haven’t slept for four nights, worried
someone might inspect the body.

6
00:00:21,500 --> 00:00:22,860
Could’ve been done sooner.

7
00:00:28,700 --> 00:00:30,280
Am I going to die?

8
00:00:33,790 --> 00:00:35,850
What… is this?

9
00:00:36,700 --> 00:00:37,920
This is real, Rann.

10
00:00:38,330 --> 00:00:39,810
P’ Le is still alive.

11
00:00:40,220 --> 00:00:41,920
I don’t know what happened.

12
00:00:43,330 --> 00:00:45,000
But it won’t end the same way this time.

13
00:00:45,690 --> 00:00:47,160
I’m going to save you.

14
00:00:47,730 --> 00:00:48,750
I promise.

15
00:01:08,130 --> 00:01:10,260
That day P’ Le told me to get out of her sight.

16
00:01:17,410 --> 00:01:22,020
After that, I went to study abroad,
determined not to come back here again.

17
00:01:24,250 --> 00:01:27,000
Five years passed without any contact between us.

18
00:01:27,039 --> 00:01:29,970
But then a gift box was delivered to my door.

19
00:01:30,030 --> 00:01:32,960
Seeing P’ Le’s handwriting,
I decided to return to Thailand.

20
00:01:34,580 --> 00:01:37,770
But when I arrived, P’ Le was…

21
00:01:59,350 --> 00:02:03,770
What I know now is that P’ Le
may have been killed by someone.

22
00:02:05,370 --> 00:02:06,820
And the person involved is…

23
00:02:16,240 --> 00:02:19,090
ASW Group appoints Ledarin Asawachun
as new Managing Director.

24
00:02:23,750 --> 00:02:25,160
He mentioned someone else.

25
00:02:27,010 --> 00:02:28,710
And then someone killed me.

26
00:02:32,660 --> 00:02:33,920
The mastermind behind it all.

27
00:02:41,700 --> 00:02:42,590
Who is he?

28
00:02:52,310 --> 00:02:53,560
If I want to find out everything...

29
00:02:56,310 --> 00:02:59,010
I have to get to the center of it first.

30
00:05:25,980 --> 00:05:27,280
Sawasdee ka, Khun Lené.

31
00:05:29,500 --> 00:05:31,420
No, no, it’s okay. I’ll get it.

32
00:05:41,510 --> 00:05:42,590
Then pick it up yourself.

33
00:05:47,960 --> 00:05:49,250
After you, Khun Lené.

34
00:06:08,930 --> 00:06:10,250
- You.
- Yes?

35
00:06:10,590 --> 00:06:11,820
When will you stop laughing?

36
00:06:12,250 --> 00:06:13,640
How could I not laugh, boss?

37
00:06:14,200 --> 00:06:15,860
You’re such a ruthless boss.

38
00:06:16,190 --> 00:06:18,520
You just dropped it when she said she’d pick it up.

39
00:06:19,740 --> 00:06:21,580
I’m sure the whole office
will be gossiping about

40
00:06:21,610 --> 00:06:24,020
how high-and-mighty Khun
Lené has a bad temper.

41
00:06:25,210 --> 00:06:27,690
But I guess it’s too late now.

42
00:06:28,520 --> 00:06:30,990
This is an office. Watch what you say.

43
00:06:31,700 --> 00:06:33,150
Are you telling yourself that, boss?

44
00:06:37,200 --> 00:06:39,810
Oh, I know that smile…

45
00:06:40,190 --> 00:06:43,380
Planning to throw in a bonus and
some vacation time for me?

46
00:06:45,190 --> 00:06:49,050
If you still want to chew
your food, then shut up.

47
00:06:56,770 --> 00:06:59,130
How scary. You think I’m scared?

48
00:07:02,740 --> 00:07:06,530
Quit fooling around and let’s get to work.
What’s on the schedule today?

49
00:07:07,630 --> 00:07:09,610
How should I know?
I’m not your secretary.

50
00:07:18,200 --> 00:07:22,860
Legal has sent over the revised contract.
They’d like your response by 1 p.m.

51
00:07:22,880 --> 00:07:25,390
There’s a meeting with
the planning team at 1 p.m.

52
00:07:25,420 --> 00:07:27,390
As for your dinner with Khun Saran this evening,

53
00:07:27,410 --> 00:07:29,900
his secretary just called
to postpone it to next week.

54
00:07:29,930 --> 00:07:33,530
He’s flying to Europe on an urgent
matter—his son’s caused trouble again.

55
00:07:33,560 --> 00:07:35,830
- Ask him if he needs any help.
- I’ve taken care of it.

56
00:07:36,659 --> 00:07:38,710
The press has been completely silenced.

57
00:07:38,890 --> 00:07:41,390
Good. The more he owes us, the better.

58
00:07:44,790 --> 00:07:47,060
See? You can do it after all.

59
00:07:58,890 --> 00:07:59,730
What else?

60
00:08:01,140 --> 00:08:02,270
Thought you wouldn’t ask.

61
00:08:04,250 --> 00:08:05,370
Don’t make that face.

62
00:08:06,230 --> 00:08:08,700
I just wanted to say that I’m—

63
00:08:08,720 --> 00:08:11,460
The head bodyguard, not
my secretary. I know that.

64
00:08:12,290 --> 00:08:13,160
So you knew.

65
00:08:13,830 --> 00:08:14,480
So?

66
00:08:15,580 --> 00:08:17,890
You can’t make me do two jobs at once.

67
00:08:18,770 --> 00:08:20,470
I could report you to the Labor Department.

68
00:08:20,640 --> 00:08:21,440
And?

69
00:08:21,710 --> 00:08:23,540
You really need to get yourself a secretary.

70
00:08:24,900 --> 00:08:27,130
Too much trouble. Nosy. Weak.

71
00:08:27,290 --> 00:08:28,610
And overly meticulous too, right?

72
00:08:29,630 --> 00:08:30,650
So you knew.

73
00:08:31,810 --> 00:08:32,850
Then go find one.

74
00:08:33,340 --> 00:08:37,080
Someone low-maintenance, not talkative,
who can keep their mouth shut.

75
00:08:37,110 --> 00:08:37,950
- And—
- Okay.

76
00:08:38,539 --> 00:08:42,580
And if I find one, my workload goes down, right?

77
00:08:46,230 --> 00:08:47,350
But it won’t be easy.

78
00:08:48,570 --> 00:08:50,910
Because the qualifications
I’m looking for in a secretary…

79
00:08:51,130 --> 00:08:53,960
Yes, I’m aware.

80
00:08:56,590 --> 00:09:00,910
First of all, they have to be punctual.
And I mean clockwork punctual.

81
00:09:01,680 --> 00:09:04,480
If you say seven o’clock,
they need to be ready by 6:30.

82
00:09:04,720 --> 00:09:06,540
I think your clock’s broken.

83
00:09:06,880 --> 00:09:12,030
Second, they have to follow every
order—no matter how irrational it is.

84
00:09:12,830 --> 00:09:14,280
Don't take it personally, boss.

85
00:09:14,480 --> 00:09:17,330
I just think some things are a bit ridiculous.

86
00:09:17,860 --> 00:09:19,680
Peem, you’re far from finished.

87
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:22,200
I also need someone who
is perfectly self-disciplined.

88
00:09:22,740 --> 00:09:26,710
Even if they finish work at 3 a.m.,
they must be ready at 6 a.m.

89
00:09:27,040 --> 00:09:28,650
without a single word of complaint.

90
00:09:32,350 --> 00:09:36,430
And the need to be fully dressed, perfectly
made up, with my schedule already in hand.

91
00:09:36,890 --> 00:09:40,330
And even if they have to wait for me
three hours, they don’t get to say a word.

92
00:09:42,080 --> 00:09:45,290
After all, your boss happens to be irrational.

93
00:09:45,870 --> 00:09:48,870
I’m aware of that. That’s why I
haven’t been able to find you a secretary.

94
00:09:49,670 --> 00:09:51,480
Because the most important qualification is…

95
00:09:52,360 --> 00:09:53,150
What’s that?

96
00:09:56,880 --> 00:09:59,210
They have to be pleasing to your eyes.

97
00:10:12,790 --> 00:10:13,800
Glad you know.

98
00:10:18,410 --> 00:10:19,820
Believe me, I know.

99
00:10:20,780 --> 00:10:24,840
Then go find one, and
your workload will be lighter.

100
00:10:27,630 --> 00:10:31,720
But if it were that easy, you’d have
found one a long time ago, right?

101
00:10:33,510 --> 00:10:35,810
You really live up to your reputation.

102
00:10:39,600 --> 00:10:43,380
Then let’s see who wins this time.

103
00:10:47,170 --> 00:10:48,060
Please come in.

104
00:11:10,490 --> 00:11:12,910
Sawasdee ka, Khun Ledarin.

105
00:11:14,840 --> 00:11:15,590
Rann.

106
00:11:16,630 --> 00:11:18,010
It’s been a long time.

107
00:11:20,390 --> 00:11:21,590
What are you doing here?

108
00:11:23,970 --> 00:11:27,410
Starting today, I’ll be taking
on the role of your secretary.

109
00:11:30,310 --> 00:11:31,810
I look forward to working with you.

110
00:11:48,960 --> 00:11:52,490
Finally, everything begins again.

111
00:11:56,170 --> 00:11:57,740
This is Khun Rann, Aran.

112
00:11:58,610 --> 00:12:00,720
She was your junior back at university.

113
00:12:00,950 --> 00:12:06,810
She holds an MBA from the UK, with two
years of experience at world-class firms.

114
00:12:07,180 --> 00:12:10,650
She’s trilingual—Thai, English, and Spanish.

115
00:12:10,930 --> 00:12:13,020
And has no issues with your working hours.

116
00:12:13,610 --> 00:12:15,030
As for her looks…

117
00:12:18,500 --> 00:12:23,840
She is the most qualified candidate
and the perfect fit for your secretary.

118
00:12:30,730 --> 00:12:31,930
I'm not approving this.

119
00:12:39,310 --> 00:12:41,420
It’s all right if you don’t
approve, Khun Ledarin,

120
00:12:42,200 --> 00:12:46,440
because Khun Kanin has already
signed my employment contract.

121
00:12:48,350 --> 00:12:49,350
My father?

122
00:12:49,770 --> 00:12:50,430
Yes.

123
00:12:51,420 --> 00:12:52,850
I look forward to working with you.

124
00:12:56,820 --> 00:12:58,360
I said I’m not approving this.

125
00:12:59,540 --> 00:13:01,310
I don’t need a secretary.

126
00:13:04,140 --> 00:13:05,460
Then I’ll begin work right away.

127
00:13:12,380 --> 00:13:16,620
You need to finish the legal review
by the end of the morning.

128
00:13:16,650 --> 00:13:20,250
The meeting materials will
be on your desk in two hours.

129
00:13:23,730 --> 00:13:25,670
If you’ll excuse me, I’ll get to work now.

130
00:13:28,290 --> 00:13:29,190
Wait.

131
00:13:35,290 --> 00:13:36,290
You know, right?

132
00:13:37,820 --> 00:13:40,600
The key requirements for being my secretary

133
00:13:41,710 --> 00:13:46,830
are to do everything I tell you to do
and be everything I want you to be.

134
00:13:50,640 --> 00:13:51,450
I’m aware.

135
00:13:53,520 --> 00:13:54,550
First of all…

136
00:13:56,510 --> 00:13:57,610
I don’t like you.

137
00:14:00,750 --> 00:14:03,350
But that’s not an instruction
on what I need to do.

138
00:14:04,440 --> 00:14:07,000
That’s a personal preference irrelevant to work.

139
00:14:07,030 --> 00:14:09,310
It contradicts my job description.

140
00:14:10,200 --> 00:14:14,640
If you have no further instructions,
I’ll excuse myself and get back to work.

141
00:14:26,770 --> 00:14:29,450
It’s quite funny to see you unable to fight back.

142
00:14:29,830 --> 00:14:30,730
Shut up.

143
00:14:46,170 --> 00:14:46,970
You ask, Sis.

144
00:14:48,740 --> 00:14:51,330
You’re the one who’s dying to know, so you ask.

145
00:14:51,480 --> 00:14:53,270
If you're so curious, go ahead and ask.

146
00:14:53,580 --> 00:14:54,610
You do it!

147
00:14:57,510 --> 00:15:01,150
Uh... hi there. My name’s Punch.

148
00:15:01,330 --> 00:15:02,940
- This is Itim.
- Sawasdee ka.

149
00:15:02,960 --> 00:15:04,190
This is Wit.

150
00:15:04,840 --> 00:15:07,350
Hey, Sis! It’s not Wit.

151
00:15:08,130 --> 00:15:09,100
I’m Vichy.

152
00:15:11,920 --> 00:15:13,310
By the way, your name is…?

153
00:15:13,670 --> 00:15:14,520
It’s Rann.

154
00:15:15,420 --> 00:15:18,000
Nong Rann. What a lovely name.

155
00:15:18,020 --> 00:15:19,800
Rann... that's so cute.

156
00:15:20,200 --> 00:15:23,230
So, are you Khun Lené’s new secretary?

157
00:15:23,870 --> 00:15:26,580
Yes, I’m taking over the position starting today.

158
00:15:27,860 --> 00:15:30,030
See? I told you! Told you so!

159
00:15:30,150 --> 00:15:31,500
- I knew it!
- For real, Momma!

160
00:15:31,660 --> 00:15:33,250
Everything you say is always spot on!

161
00:15:33,480 --> 00:15:34,820
Did I even say anything?!

162
00:15:35,600 --> 00:15:37,220
Well, you didn't believe P' Punch.

163
00:15:37,450 --> 00:15:38,900
You said she was just delusional

164
00:15:38,920 --> 00:15:41,330
and that no one in their right mind
would want to be Khun Lené’s secretary.

165
00:15:42,730 --> 00:15:43,730
Am I wrong though?

166
00:15:43,900 --> 00:15:47,640
That woman is as ruthless as a mob boss.
She uses people like machines!

167
00:15:49,130 --> 00:15:52,050
Oh! No, no, Nong Rann.
Don’t get the wrong idea.

168
00:15:52,070 --> 00:15:54,990
We’re not gossiping about the boss.
We’re just curious.

169
00:15:55,250 --> 00:15:56,050
Exactly, Momma.

170
00:15:56,870 --> 00:15:58,660
So… is there something you need?

171
00:15:58,680 --> 00:16:01,220
Goodness, Nong Rann!
What do you mean 'need something'?

172
00:16:01,240 --> 00:16:03,700
You're overthinking it.
We just wanted to get to know the new girl.

173
00:16:03,720 --> 00:16:04,730
Total facts, Momma.

174
00:16:05,300 --> 00:16:08,970
So, how did you manage to
become Khun Lené’s secretary?

175
00:16:09,140 --> 00:16:13,060
Do you know the last one didn’t even last for—

176
00:16:14,360 --> 00:16:16,610
Oh! Khun Lené! Sawasdee ka.

177
00:16:16,720 --> 00:16:18,740
Um, we should really get going.
Vichy is having a—

178
00:16:19,680 --> 00:16:21,310
- Are you okay?
- No, not okay!

179
00:16:21,340 --> 00:16:22,670
- Come on, let’s go.
- I’m sick. Very sick.

180
00:16:22,690 --> 00:16:23,750
Please excuse us.

181
00:16:35,210 --> 00:16:37,130
Do you need anything, Khun Ledarin?

182
00:16:38,870 --> 00:16:40,320
‘Ledarin.’ How formal.

183
00:16:43,000 --> 00:16:45,750
Then what would you like me to call you?

184
00:16:46,850 --> 00:16:49,060
It’s nothing. Forget it.

185
00:17:03,670 --> 00:17:04,619
Listen.

186
00:17:05,829 --> 00:17:10,450
I don't need a secretary,
and I never approved you to be mine.

187
00:17:12,150 --> 00:17:13,280
I can't do that either.

188
00:17:13,720 --> 00:17:17,780
I have a contract with your father, and
I’m not risking a breach of contract suit.

189
00:17:18,770 --> 00:17:24,599
Therefore, as long as I perform my duties,
you have no right to fire me either.

190
00:17:30,760 --> 00:17:32,590
Do you really think I can't fire you?

191
00:17:34,350 --> 00:17:35,540
That's not what I'm saying.

192
00:17:36,630 --> 00:17:38,270
But as long as I’ve done nothing wrong,

193
00:17:39,100 --> 00:17:43,720
I must inform you that you have
no grounds to dismiss me either.

194
00:17:51,670 --> 00:17:54,500
We’ll see about that... Aran.

195
00:18:11,840 --> 00:18:14,970
I didn't think I’d be this
close to you again, P’ Le.

196
00:18:21,040 --> 00:18:22,510
I can't give up.

197
00:18:39,210 --> 00:18:40,970
Okay, let’s recap.

198
00:18:41,650 --> 00:18:43,720
There’s a meeting this morning until 11.

199
00:18:44,310 --> 00:18:48,100
Afternoon, clear the paperwork
and then back to meetings.

200
00:19:25,830 --> 00:19:26,880
Why isn't she here yet?

201
00:19:39,830 --> 00:19:41,760
I think you’re being messed with, Khun Rann.

202
00:19:46,790 --> 00:19:48,260
Where is Khun Ledarin?

203
00:19:49,340 --> 00:19:50,350
I don't know.

204
00:19:50,910 --> 00:19:53,520
She said she was coming in by herself
and didn't need a bodyguard.

205
00:20:00,140 --> 00:20:02,310
I thought you’d last more than two weeks.

206
00:20:03,050 --> 00:20:04,160
Don’t give up yet.

207
00:20:06,190 --> 00:20:07,310
I put a big bet on you.

208
00:20:17,160 --> 00:20:17,950
What?

209
00:20:36,810 --> 00:20:39,240
Wake up, please. It's already 10:30.

210
00:20:53,670 --> 00:20:56,470
Have you forgotten that you have
a meeting this morning, Khun Ledarin?

211
00:20:56,750 --> 00:21:00,150
I’ve already notified all parties
and rescheduled the meeting for you.

212
00:21:00,400 --> 00:21:04,080
You need to get up, shower, and get dressed.

213
00:21:05,650 --> 00:21:07,490
Not doing it. I’m not in the mood.

214
00:21:09,650 --> 00:21:10,830
Khun Ledarin!

215
00:21:58,130 --> 00:21:59,210
I won’t do it.

216
00:22:01,090 --> 00:22:01,900
Is that clear?

217
00:22:05,190 --> 00:22:06,040
Yes.

218
00:22:08,440 --> 00:22:10,670
That’s why I moved
the schedule for you, Khun Ledarin.

219
00:22:13,230 --> 00:22:16,330
Enough with the 'Ledarin.'

220
00:22:17,540 --> 00:22:19,250
Do you think I’ve forgotten my own name?

221
00:22:20,470 --> 00:22:24,450
Then… what should I call you?

222
00:22:29,210 --> 00:22:32,960
Khun Le... Né?

223
00:22:45,240 --> 00:22:46,970
Get out of my sight.

224
00:23:03,140 --> 00:23:06,270
Then let go of me, so I can do exactly that.

225
00:23:15,990 --> 00:23:19,810
But you only have one hour to get ready.
That’s as much time as I could buy you.

226
00:23:46,090 --> 00:23:48,410
Do I need to praise you for your patience?

227
00:23:49,100 --> 00:23:51,570
You’re good. Extremely good.

228
00:23:55,530 --> 00:23:57,150
Thank you for the compliment.

229
00:23:59,080 --> 00:24:03,790
I'll compensate you for it... once I fire you.

230
00:24:06,930 --> 00:24:08,530
That won't be happening today.

231
00:24:09,420 --> 00:24:10,670
You're awfully confident.

232
00:24:12,180 --> 00:24:16,340
You don't even have what it takes
to get me to a meeting.

233
00:24:28,270 --> 00:24:31,900
Just because you aren't going into the office
doesn't mean you can't join the meeting.

234
00:24:37,970 --> 00:24:38,980
Holy hell!

235
00:24:47,140 --> 00:24:49,440
Get on with it!
Don't just sit there staring.

236
00:24:50,160 --> 00:24:51,160
You’re wasting my time.

237
00:24:51,340 --> 00:24:53,000
Okay, let’s get started.

238
00:25:04,000 --> 00:25:05,990
Would you like this, Khun Ledarin?

239
00:25:27,610 --> 00:25:28,580
Put it on.

240
00:25:32,950 --> 00:25:33,830
Lené.

241
00:25:36,240 --> 00:25:37,620
Just call me Lené.

242
00:25:43,400 --> 00:25:45,620
Yes, Khun Lené.

243
00:25:47,710 --> 00:25:49,190
Have a safe ride.

244
00:25:50,450 --> 00:25:52,650
Stop smiling like that. I don’t like it.

245
00:25:53,060 --> 00:25:53,960
I’m sorry.

246
00:26:00,770 --> 00:26:02,070
- I'll be off then.
- Okay.

247
00:26:29,540 --> 00:26:30,530
Come into my office.

248
00:26:42,540 --> 00:26:43,420
What is this?

249
00:26:46,340 --> 00:26:49,050
The documents you need
to finish reviewing by today.

250
00:26:50,330 --> 00:26:53,970
I mean, why are they piled up in such a mess?

251
00:26:56,980 --> 00:27:00,470
I don't need a secretary who does sloppy work.

252
00:27:02,960 --> 00:27:05,670
I apologize for the disorganized
state of the documents.

253
00:27:07,620 --> 00:27:08,630
Good that you know.

254
00:27:09,020 --> 00:27:14,750
In that case, I’ll organize them neatly
instead of prioritizing urgency next time.

255
00:27:24,890 --> 00:27:26,700
I’ve already screened them.

256
00:27:27,150 --> 00:27:32,670
Since they have different levels of
urgency, I sorted them by priority.

257
00:27:34,570 --> 00:27:35,940
I’ll re-sort them for you.

258
00:27:36,170 --> 00:27:37,020
Get out.

259
00:27:37,890 --> 00:27:38,720
Pardon?

260
00:27:39,730 --> 00:27:41,990
I have work to do. Out.

261
00:27:42,340 --> 00:27:43,660
But the documents are still—

262
00:27:43,720 --> 00:27:45,180
I said out.

263
00:28:00,410 --> 00:28:01,980
Gather more data.

264
00:28:02,570 --> 00:28:06,450
The company isn’t pouring money into
this product until there’s proven feedback.

265
00:28:08,640 --> 00:28:10,410
Send me the report next week.
Can you manage?

266
00:28:12,050 --> 00:28:12,850
Yes.

267
00:28:14,680 --> 00:28:15,490
Where’s the pen?

268
00:28:17,920 --> 00:28:19,010
Why didn't you prepare one?

269
00:28:21,640 --> 00:28:26,090
Sorry. I remember you used to take notes
on your tablet, so I prepared this for you.

270
00:28:27,720 --> 00:28:31,230
And this is the file for today's meeting.
You can take notes in here.

271
00:28:32,610 --> 00:28:35,550
Next time, I'll have a pen
and paper ready for you.

272
00:28:38,640 --> 00:28:39,620
Don’t bother.

273
00:28:46,150 --> 00:28:49,580
If there’s a problem, it should be fine.
Khun Lené will probably just cancel it.

274
00:28:52,140 --> 00:28:54,940
Tell Peem to get the car ready.
I'm going to the warehouse.

275
00:28:55,740 --> 00:28:58,860
It’s already done.
Khun Peem is waiting with the car downstairs.

276
00:29:01,740 --> 00:29:04,280
I’ve already put all the documents in the car.

277
00:29:04,960 --> 00:29:06,610
You can review them on the way.

278
00:29:07,610 --> 00:29:08,970
Always one step ahead, aren’t you?

279
00:29:09,740 --> 00:29:11,270
Because I don't want to lose my job.

280
00:29:25,390 --> 00:29:26,930
- Nong Rann, Nong Rann.
- Nong Rann.

281
00:29:30,190 --> 00:29:31,190
Can I ask you something?

282
00:29:31,880 --> 00:29:34,290
What’s your secret for dealing with Khun Lené?

283
00:29:34,310 --> 00:29:37,730
I mean, you’re absolutely slaying it.

284
00:29:41,220 --> 00:29:43,260
I'm just doing my work as usual.

285
00:29:43,670 --> 00:29:47,840
Oh, stop lying.
That’s what we call being a professional.

286
00:29:48,070 --> 00:29:51,360
Like, total pro. Next level.
God-tier. You’re the GOAT!

287
00:29:51,600 --> 00:29:53,770
What goat? Is someone raising a goat?

288
00:30:10,300 --> 00:30:12,120
When are you finally coming back to Thailand?

289
00:30:14,470 --> 00:30:15,790
Not right now.

290
00:30:24,350 --> 00:30:25,380
It’s not time yet.

291
00:30:25,610 --> 00:30:27,950
Gen

292
00:30:26,230 --> 00:30:27,950
So when will that be?

293
00:30:28,830 --> 00:30:31,100
When you got the scholarship,
you left so suddenly.

294
00:30:31,640 --> 00:30:34,420
All you said was that you had
to prepare yourself for P’ Le.

295
00:30:35,010 --> 00:30:36,010
Prepare for what?

296
00:30:38,730 --> 00:30:40,090
Seriously, Rann.

297
00:30:41,030 --> 00:30:43,930
Why didn’t you and P’Le just
make it official once and for all?

298
00:30:44,850 --> 00:30:47,030
What really happened on graduation day?

299
00:30:49,530 --> 00:30:51,620
I promise I'll tell you everything.

300
00:30:52,860 --> 00:30:53,960
It's just...

301
00:30:55,820 --> 00:30:56,890
Forget it.

302
00:30:57,090 --> 00:31:00,300
I can’t even handle my own
problems, so I'll stay out of yours.

303
00:31:02,210 --> 00:31:03,800
As for what you asked me to look into.

304
00:31:03,950 --> 00:31:08,240
I've emailed you all the info I could find
on people who used to work with P’Le.

305
00:31:10,520 --> 00:31:14,270
But... I don't know. Over the years,
there’s been something strange about P’Le.

306
00:31:14,560 --> 00:31:18,020
People say she’s demanding,
hard to work with, and mean.

307
00:31:18,160 --> 00:31:19,980
Anyone who crosses her gets fired immediately.

308
00:31:20,010 --> 00:31:21,740
And she doesn't even socialize with anyone.

309
00:31:29,290 --> 00:31:30,970
I simply prepared in advance.

310
00:31:33,110 --> 00:31:34,310
Two lifetimes in advance.

311
00:31:35,180 --> 00:31:36,180
Prepare what?

312
00:31:36,580 --> 00:31:38,230
I should get back to work now.

313
00:31:39,160 --> 00:31:40,120
- Alright.
- Okay.

314
00:31:45,120 --> 00:31:46,280
Seriously, Sis.

315
00:31:46,300 --> 00:31:49,590
We’d need a whole a past life
just to prep for Khun Lené.

316
00:31:50,190 --> 00:31:52,990
We prepped all week and
she still bit our heads off.

317
00:31:53,110 --> 00:31:55,360
When did it happen? I had no idea.

318
00:32:29,210 --> 00:32:34,220
Following me home even after hours...
What a perfect secretary you are.

319
00:32:34,920 --> 00:32:36,430
Thank you for the compliment.

320
00:32:39,160 --> 00:32:40,250
That wasn't a compliment.

321
00:32:41,080 --> 00:32:42,030
I know.

322
00:32:44,070 --> 00:32:45,080
You can leave now.

323
00:32:46,710 --> 00:32:47,850
Wait, P’ Le.

324
00:33:09,880 --> 00:33:12,990
I mean… Khun Lené.

325
00:33:15,000 --> 00:33:18,870
If there’s anything you’d like me
to improve, please just let me know.

326
00:33:19,190 --> 00:33:21,610
I’ll adapt to fit your working style.

327
00:33:24,380 --> 00:33:27,190
So you actually realized I don't like it?

328
00:33:27,630 --> 00:33:31,120
And have you realized you’ve been
watching for my every mistake for days now?

329
00:33:33,090 --> 00:33:34,120
I’m being serious.

330
00:33:36,090 --> 00:33:37,110
Why did you come back?

331
00:33:38,070 --> 00:33:39,320
What exactly do you want?

332
00:33:44,850 --> 00:33:46,760
Do you think I'm doing my job well, Khun Lené?

333
00:33:51,470 --> 00:33:53,690
Good enough to be the one by your side...

334
00:34:00,480 --> 00:34:02,230
instead of Khun Peem?

335
00:34:08,090 --> 00:34:09,630
You're eyeing Peem's position now?

336
00:34:14,350 --> 00:34:15,429
Who do you think you are?

337
00:34:17,500 --> 00:34:19,030
Do you even know who he is?

338
00:34:19,320 --> 00:34:20,679
And do you?

339
00:34:21,650 --> 00:34:22,659
Don't talk back to me.

340
00:34:24,080 --> 00:34:26,030
I’m asking why you aren't working abroad.

341
00:34:27,770 --> 00:34:28,790
Why did you come back?

342
00:34:30,860 --> 00:34:32,590
Because the compensation is high.

343
00:34:35,159 --> 00:34:36,409
Don’t worry.

344
00:34:37,030 --> 00:34:41,810
Even though it's already midnight, I'll still
be getting overtime at the end of the month.

345
00:34:43,170 --> 00:34:48,000
If you want to get your money’s worth,
please feel free to use me however you like.

346
00:34:49,280 --> 00:34:50,560
I'm not worried about you.

347
00:34:52,239 --> 00:34:53,409
I know that too.

348
00:34:55,449 --> 00:34:57,010
And I never will.

349
00:34:59,230 --> 00:35:01,130
You won't get what you want.

350
00:35:04,770 --> 00:35:08,210
Bear that in mind... Miss Secretary.

351
00:35:15,260 --> 00:35:18,840
I’m aware of that as well… P’ Le.

352
00:35:38,790 --> 00:35:40,320
Why did you come back, Rann?

353
00:35:42,090 --> 00:35:43,570
I pushed you away so hard.

354
00:35:45,760 --> 00:35:47,790
Why come back just to let me hurt you again?

355
00:35:56,520 --> 00:35:57,970
I won’t give up.

356
00:36:00,810 --> 00:36:02,020
I can’t give up.

357
00:36:27,390 --> 00:36:28,400
Do me a favor.

358
00:36:47,570 --> 00:36:49,390
Where are you headed?
Let me give you a lift.

359
00:36:50,890 --> 00:36:51,970
I can get back on my own.

360
00:36:51,990 --> 00:36:55,430
I can’t let you do that.
It’s an order from Khun Lené.

361
00:36:57,840 --> 00:36:59,740
She called to wake me up at midnight for this.

362
00:37:01,190 --> 00:37:04,570
I was having a sweet dream
about a full month off,

363
00:37:04,910 --> 00:37:07,080
but there’s no going back to sleep after that.

364
00:37:07,630 --> 00:37:12,720
And if I head back now, Khun Lené
will kick me out for disobeying orders.

365
00:37:15,280 --> 00:37:17,310
You live in the same house as her?

366
00:37:17,700 --> 00:37:19,270
Well, well.

367
00:37:21,100 --> 00:37:23,100
Starting to get interested in me now?

368
00:37:26,590 --> 00:37:27,650
And your point is?

369
00:37:28,130 --> 00:37:29,270
Why don’t we…

370
00:37:31,960 --> 00:37:33,380
continue this conversation in the car?

371
00:37:39,300 --> 00:37:40,890
Fine, I’ll open the door for you.

372
00:37:44,610 --> 00:37:45,770
After you, milady.

373
00:38:07,810 --> 00:38:08,810
Candy?

374
00:38:11,230 --> 00:38:13,390
Do you really live in
the same house as Khun Lené?

375
00:38:16,250 --> 00:38:20,020
Now I see why the boss
has such a soft spot for you.

376
00:38:23,600 --> 00:38:24,380
Yes.

377
00:38:26,310 --> 00:38:28,390
We've lived in the same house for years now.

378
00:38:30,030 --> 00:38:32,680
Even longer, if you count
the years I've worked for her.

379
00:38:34,830 --> 00:38:40,930
But even in all that time, I’ve never
seen the boss have a soft spot for anyone.

380
00:38:46,640 --> 00:38:51,390
I'm telling you this as a colleague who'll
be working with you for years to come.

381
00:38:54,230 --> 00:38:57,640
The secretary before you didn't even last a week.

382
00:38:58,370 --> 00:39:02,250
I’ve seen with my own eyes
how she tears people apart.

383
00:39:03,790 --> 00:39:05,050
But with you...

384
00:39:06,360 --> 00:39:09,100
She’s like a child playing house.

385
00:39:09,730 --> 00:39:11,590
That’s why I said she has a soft spot for you.

386
00:39:16,300 --> 00:39:17,300
That's not true.

387
00:39:21,440 --> 00:39:24,060
Okay. It's fine if you don't believe me.

388
00:39:24,920 --> 00:39:28,010
Then let’s stop gossiping about the boss...

389
00:39:29,650 --> 00:39:31,180
and get back to talking about us.

390
00:39:34,300 --> 00:39:35,930
There is no 'us'.

391
00:39:36,160 --> 00:39:37,090
But there is.

392
00:39:39,260 --> 00:39:40,220
Like the fact that...

393
00:39:42,220 --> 00:39:43,700
you don’t like me.

394
00:39:47,150 --> 00:39:49,190
You can look over the offer first.

395
00:39:50,220 --> 00:39:50,960
Thank you.

396
00:40:06,770 --> 00:40:08,540
May I be frank with you?

397
00:40:09,180 --> 00:40:09,960
Of course.

398
00:40:11,540 --> 00:40:13,280
Why did you choose to hire me, Khun Kanin?

399
00:40:14,420 --> 00:40:19,640
I’m sure there are countless people
more qualified to be Khun Ledarin’s secretary.

400
00:40:21,100 --> 00:40:23,310
If I’m being honest, you’re right.

401
00:40:24,660 --> 00:40:28,860
There are so many people qualified
to be my daughter’s secretary

402
00:40:29,610 --> 00:40:32,470
that it was actually hard to choose.

403
00:40:33,320 --> 00:40:34,890
But out of all the applicants,

404
00:40:36,280 --> 00:40:39,330
you’re the one with the most
time to take care of my daughter.

405
00:40:42,760 --> 00:40:44,450
Is it because I don't have a family?

406
00:40:48,630 --> 00:40:53,520
If you look on the bright side... it means
you can focus entirely on your work.

407
00:40:54,950 --> 00:40:59,100
As for the compensation, I’ll
make sure it’s well worth your while.

408
00:41:11,360 --> 00:41:14,560
Will I be expected to do anything
beyond my secretarial duties?

409
00:41:16,930 --> 00:41:19,870
It’s just... the salary is a bit too high.

410
00:41:23,970 --> 00:41:30,520
As a father, I’m deeply
worried about my only daughter.

411
00:41:32,350 --> 00:41:35,630
And she’s a very strong-willed person.

412
00:41:37,670 --> 00:41:40,860
As expected of an only child.

413
00:41:41,990 --> 00:41:43,800
She’s been spoiled since she was little.

414
00:41:45,120 --> 00:41:48,350
Which is why she doesn't
really listen to my advice.

415
00:41:49,740 --> 00:41:52,560
All I can do is worry about her from afar.

416
00:41:54,390 --> 00:41:55,710
Let's get straight to the point.

417
00:41:57,790 --> 00:42:01,410
I just want to know what my daughter is up to.

418
00:42:03,150 --> 00:42:08,840
Your responsibility is to give me
a report on everything she does.

419
00:42:12,510 --> 00:42:13,630
You can do it, right?

420
00:42:32,920 --> 00:42:35,010
This brings me much
closer to P’ Le than I thought.

421
00:42:38,010 --> 00:42:39,550
Now that you've taken the job,

422
00:42:41,170 --> 00:42:43,280
you should meet your colleague.

423
00:42:57,380 --> 00:42:59,710
I’m Peem. Nice to meet you.

424
00:43:09,870 --> 00:43:13,210
Yes. I don’t like you.

425
00:43:16,120 --> 00:43:17,720
Okay. I give up.

426
00:43:19,440 --> 00:43:21,430
I have no idea what I did to make you hate me,

427
00:43:22,030 --> 00:43:24,290
but there’s not much
I can do about it, is there?

428
00:43:27,510 --> 00:43:28,830
But even if you hate me…

429
00:43:30,590 --> 00:43:33,780
I’m still glad to have you on the team.

430
00:43:36,700 --> 00:43:42,860
It isn't often that we get to see the ‘high
and mighty’ Khun Lené look so flustered.

431
00:43:43,380 --> 00:43:46,510
I tried so hard not to laugh
every time she was with you.

432
00:43:48,210 --> 00:43:49,530
You think this is funny?

433
00:43:50,110 --> 00:43:55,220
Come on, my job is stressful.
I need some entertainment once in a while.

434
00:43:56,570 --> 00:44:01,690
When I applied, I didn't realize it meant
being a full-time bodyguard, glued to her hip.

435
00:44:02,380 --> 00:44:05,490
And have to live under the same
roof as well. Just my luck.

436
00:44:08,820 --> 00:44:09,940
I’ll leave these with you.

437
00:44:10,550 --> 00:44:11,930
I'll handle it from here.

438
00:44:12,130 --> 00:44:15,590
Just let me know if you want anything
else, and I’ll take care of it for you.

439
00:44:16,210 --> 00:44:16,990
Thank you.

440
00:44:17,950 --> 00:44:20,830
What’s all this commotion?
And what is all this luggage?

441
00:44:25,840 --> 00:44:26,940
I’ll handle this.

442
00:44:27,660 --> 00:44:28,420
Okay.

443
00:44:33,610 --> 00:44:37,000
What are you doing in my house
this early, ordering my staff around?

444
00:44:38,490 --> 00:44:41,450
Starting today, I’m moving into your house.

445
00:44:41,810 --> 00:44:42,850
Who gave you permission?

446
00:44:43,510 --> 00:44:44,590
Your father.

447
00:44:47,030 --> 00:44:50,160
This is my house, not my father’s.

448
00:44:51,130 --> 00:44:52,760
And I'm the one who owns it.

449
00:44:53,830 --> 00:44:57,170
Am I supposed to just
roll over and accept his order?

450
00:44:59,040 --> 00:45:03,050
I don't recall ever inviting
you to stay in this house.

451
00:45:04,110 --> 00:45:08,480
In fact… I never invited you
to set foot in this place.

452
00:45:10,330 --> 00:45:11,960
Let alone barge into my life.

453
00:45:18,120 --> 00:45:19,950
I’m just doing what I was assigned to do.

454
00:45:20,810 --> 00:45:21,910
I never asked for this.

455
00:45:22,220 --> 00:45:23,760
You’re being unreasonable, Khun Lené.

456
00:45:25,750 --> 00:45:27,320
Who exactly is being unreasonable here?

457
00:45:28,550 --> 00:45:29,720
I’m asking you.

458
00:45:30,160 --> 00:45:32,390
When did I ever invite you back into my life?!

459
00:45:35,200 --> 00:45:36,640
You can act like you don't know me.

460
00:45:38,440 --> 00:45:42,420
Because I’d be more than
happy to do the same for you.

461
00:45:43,790 --> 00:45:45,240
We don't need to know each other.

462
00:45:46,740 --> 00:45:48,120
I can tolerate you for work.

463
00:45:48,790 --> 00:45:50,210
But this is my private life!

464
00:45:51,170 --> 00:45:54,590
Has no one ever taught you
to mind your own business?

465
00:45:54,770 --> 00:45:56,180
I’m not meddling in your business.

466
00:45:59,750 --> 00:46:03,430
Everything I’ve done is strictly for work.

467
00:46:05,270 --> 00:46:08,770
If you didn't act so childish
by refusing to get up for work,

468
00:46:08,790 --> 00:46:10,650
I wouldn't have to resort to this.

469
00:46:12,270 --> 00:46:15,540
And when you told me to forget...

470
00:46:16,550 --> 00:46:20,320
isn’t it actually you who's
remembering everything?

471
00:46:22,570 --> 00:46:25,630
You’re the one blurring the line
between work and personal feelings.

472
00:46:25,790 --> 00:46:26,610
Rann!

473
00:46:30,280 --> 00:46:31,860
So you still remember my name?

474
00:46:33,390 --> 00:46:34,820
I told you already, didn't I?

475
00:46:36,110 --> 00:46:37,450
Get out of my sight!

476
00:46:42,380 --> 00:46:43,640
It’s only been four years.

477
00:46:46,420 --> 00:46:47,620
Have you forgotten already?

478
00:46:53,840 --> 00:47:00,040
I’m glad you still remember exactly
how many years it’s been, Khun Ledarin.

479
00:47:02,670 --> 00:47:05,610
No… P’ Le.

480
00:47:13,510 --> 00:47:14,320
Yes.

481
00:47:16,060 --> 00:47:17,550
I used to be your P’ Le.

482
00:47:20,570 --> 00:47:22,220
But that’s not the case anymore.

483
00:47:26,020 --> 00:47:27,340
Make sure you remember that.

484
00:47:29,770 --> 00:47:31,860
I’ve kicked you out of my life once before.

485
00:47:34,500 --> 00:47:38,510
What makes you think I can't do it again?

486
00:49:01,650 --> 00:49:03,210
Why are you doing this?

487
00:49:04,750 --> 00:49:05,780
Wait, P’ Le.

488
00:49:47,220 --> 00:49:50,220
English Subtitles by Saowalak K.

489
00:49:50,520 --> 00:49:52,090
- Wait a second! Oh!
- Khun Rann!

490
00:49:54,390 --> 00:49:57,470
If you can’t handle high heels,
then don’t wear them again.

491
00:49:57,630 --> 00:50:00,360
Do you know why Khun Lené
changed her car, Khun Rann?

492
00:50:00,980 --> 00:50:04,680
I once told my grandma that
after I graduate and get a job,

493
00:50:05,200 --> 00:50:09,260
I'll buy a big car so I can drive her everywhere.

494
00:50:09,910 --> 00:50:12,580
There’s someone I’d like to introduce to you all.

495
00:50:17,940 --> 00:50:21,500
Hello, everyone. I’m Dean Dithakorn.

496
00:50:26,770 --> 00:50:27,830
Don’t tell me…

497
00:50:30,730 --> 00:50:31,690
You’re jealous.
